BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:o0s0GkvDikDs3bcn2bpeb
SUMMARY:Inside the Clerkship
DTSTAMP:20260315T234229Z
DTSTART:20260316T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an exclusive and candid panel discussion featuring 
	distinguished judges and former and current law clerks who will demystify 
	the clerkship application process. Designed for law students at all stages
	\, this event offers firsthand insight into what judges look for in applic
	ants\, how to stand out in a competitive pool\, and how to strategically p
	repare throughout law school.\n\n \n\nPanelists will share practical advic
	e on building strong relationships with faculty\, crafting compelling appl
	ication materials\, navigating interviews\, and positioning yourself for b
	oth state and federal clerkships. Attendees will also gain valuable perspe
	ctive on what life is like inside chambers and how a clerkship can shape l
	ong-term career trajectories.\n\n \n\nIn addition\, this program will prev
	iew the Federal Litigation course offered in Fall 2026. Attendees will lea
	rn how the course strengthens the research\, writing\, and advocacy skills
	 that judges value most in clerkship candidates\, and how it can position 
	students for success in competitive judicial hiring.\n\n \n\nWhether you'r
	e just beginning to consider a clerkship or preparing to apply\, this prog
	ram will provide actionable guidance\, insider tips\, and an opportunity t
	o ask questions directly to those involved in the hiring process—while off
	ering a forward-looking glimpse at how the upcoming Federal Litigation cou
	rse can support your goals.\n\n \n\nPanelists:\n\nJudge Roopali Desai\, Un
	ited States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit\n\nJudge Kymberly Evans
	on\, United States District Court for the Western District of Washington\n
	\nJudge Jamal Whitehead\, United States District Court for the Western Dis
	trict of Washington\n\nLuther Reed-Caulkins\, Current Judicial Law Clerk t
	o the Honorable Kymberly Evanson\n\nRuby Nagamine\, Current Judicial Law C
	lerk to the Honorable Richard A. Jones\, United States District Court for 
	the Western District of Washington\n\nDalvin Yarbrough\, Former Judicial L
	aw Clerk for The Honorable Reggie B. Walton\, United States District Court
	 for the District of Columbia\, 2023-2025\n\nModerator:\n\nCynthia Jones\,
	 Jones Legal Group and Adjunct Professor\, Seattle University School of La
	w \\(Federal Litigation\\) \n\n \n\nDate: March 16th\, 2026\n\nTime: 4:00 
	PM to 5:30 PM\n\nLocation: Sullivan Hall\, Room 110\n\nhttps://seatoday.6a
	mcity.com/events/#/details/inside-the-clerkship/18260245/2026-03-16T00\n\n
	From SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/inside-the-clerkship/1826
	0245/2026-03-16T00
LOCATION:Sullivan Hall\, 110\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
